Dellius was a man of fickle and inconstant character, who is said to have changed sides four times during the civil wars- When this ode was written he seems to have been in a state of dejection, on account of the condition of his affairs. The poet exhorts him to preserve equanimity of temper under all circum- stances 3 since the shortness of life renders it of comparatively little importance whether a man be rich or poor.
